title: ReallyAnnoyingFiveFactorAuthenticationProcess
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

The Really Annoying Five-Factor Authentication Process (RAFFAP) is required to access the [[Employee Information System]] on Tuesdays (unless you've bought coffee from the cafeteria that day).

The five factors are:

# Password (minimum 32 characters, changed monthly)
# SMS code to your company phone
# Email confirmation link to your company email
# A second email confirmation to your personal email on file
# Manager approval via the manager's own authenticated portal

The approval chain for step 5 means authentication can take up to 24 hours if your manager is out of office. Plan accordingly for Tuesday EIS tasks.

JaneDoe walked me through the process during my onboarding as part of the EmployeeProfileSetupMeeting.
